I'm trying to make a program that counts the multiples of fives, but skips the multiples of 7. Ex: 25 30 40  Also I want it to ask if you want to enter new numbers and repeat until you say no. It mostly works but I have 2 problems. When you enter a non multiple of five for the larger number it doesn't ask you if you want to enter new numbers and I can't figure out how to end the program after entering no.

    start = int(input("Enter the starting number: "))
    end = int(input("Enter the ending number: "))
    replay = ""

    while start %5 != 0:
        start+= 1

    while True:
        while start <= end:
            if start % end <= 1:
                replay = input("\nwould you like to enter new numbers? [y or n] ")

                if replay == 'y':
                    start = int(input("Enter the starting number: "))
                    end = int(input("Enter the ending number: "))
                    while start %5 != 0:
                        start+= 1

                elif replay != 'y':
                    print("Okay bye")
                    #tried break here 

            if start > end:
                print("Error! Starting value cannot be larger than ending value.")

            if start % 7 !=0:
                print(start, end=" ")
                start+= 5

            elif start %7 ==0:
                start+= 5


    input("\n\nPress the enter key to exit.")

comments.body:
Classic interview question.

The problem with your break not working is that you have too many loops, and break/continue only works on the immediate one you're in.

note: to post code to reddit, indent the whole block an extra time. Otherwise reddit will strip formatting. 

Ok, so if you move the loops around a little, I think it fixes your problem! This works, and changes only 1-2 lines of your code.

    start = int(input("Enter the starting number: "))
    end = int(input("Enter the ending number: "))
    replay = ""
    while start %5 != 0:
        start+= 1

    while True:
        if start >= end:
            replay = input("\nwould you like to enter new numbers? [y or n] ")
            if replay == 'y':
                start = int(input("Enter the starting number: "))
                end = int(input("Enter the ending number: "))
                while start %5 != 0:
                    start+= 1
            elif replay != 'y':
                print("Okay bye")
                #Tried putting break here and now it does work!
                break

        while start <= end:
            if start > end:
                print("Error! Starting value cannot be larger than ending value.")
            if start % 7 !=0:
                print(start, end=" ")
                start+= 5
            elif start %7 ==0:
                start+= 5
    input("\n\nPress the enter key to exit.")
